# VM Setup Guide for CompTIA Security+ (SY0-701)

## Objective
Set up a virtual machine (VM) with Ubuntu for practicing cybersecurity skills for CompTIA Security+ (SY0-701).

## Tools
- **VirtualBox**: Free virtualization software.
- **Ubuntu**: Linux OS (LTS version, e.g., 24.04).

## Steps

### 1. Install VirtualBox
- Download from [virtualbox.org](https://www.virtualbox.org).
- Run installer, accept defaults, and complete setup.
- Optional: Install Extension Pack for extra features.

### 2. Download Ubuntu
- Get the latest LTS .iso from [ubuntu.com/download/desktop](https://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop).

### 3. Create VM in VirtualBox
- Click "New" in VirtualBox.
- Name: Ubuntu_SecurityPlus
- Type: Linux, Version: Ubuntu (64-bit)
- RAM: 2-4 GB
- Disk: Create VDI, dynamically allocated, 20-30 GB

### 4. Configure VM
- Settings > Storage > Add Ubuntu .iso to Controller: IDE.
- Network > Adapter 1: Enable, set to NAT.
- Save settings.

### 5. Install Ubuntu
- Start VM, select "Install Ubuntu."
- Follow prompts: language, keyboard, erase disk (virtual), set username/password.
- Reboot after installation.

### 6. Test
- Log in to Ubuntu.
- Run `sudo apt update` in terminal to verify functionality.

## Notes
- Completed setup, as part of Security+ prep.
- Environment ready for security tools, labs, and SY0-701 practice!

